{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 684065, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rozenberg", "body": "The fight against Thorim is split between two phases. The first one requires you to fight your way to Thorim by fighting multiple types of trash mobs in the Arena, the second one will let you face Thorim himself. \r\n\r\nThe first part of the fight is split in 3 mini-phases (Jormungar > Iron Dwarves > Hallway). Thorim will use a few abilities during the arena event, do not bother attacking him because he is protected by Sheath of Lightning.\r\n\r\nYou will first encounter a Jormungar Behemoth and a few NPCs from the opposite faction fighting in the Arena.\r\n\r\nOnce the NPCs and the Jormungar are dead, a lot of constructs (melee, casters, and healers) will jump into the arena from the stands and you will have to take care of them with only one part of your raid while the other part runs through the hallway on the left to reach Thorim.\r\n\r\nAs soon as you reach Thorim at the end of the hallway, he will jump in the Arena where the first part of your raid is and will engage them.\r\n\r\n[b]Hard Mode - Sif[/b]\r\nIf you reach Thorim within 3 minutes, he will not be affected by Touch of Dominion and have 25% more damage and health. Additionally, he will be helped by his wife Sif. You cannot kill her, she will just attack the raid while you're fighting Thorim.", "date": "2009-04-19T02:38:46-05:00", "rating": 48, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Note that the \"arena team\" healing and tanking is much easier when you have Mass Dispel / Spellsteal.", "creationdate": "2009-05-03T14:35:38-05:00", "id": 95681, "rating": 26, "commentid": 684065, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "290438", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]Hard Mode - Sif If you reach Thorim within 3 minutes, he will not be affected by Touch of Dominion and have 25% more damage and health. Additionally, he will be helped by his [u]wife[/u] Sif. You cannot kill her, she will just attack the raid while you're fighting Thorim. [/quote]  A married raider's worst nightmare: [b][u]WIFE AGGRO[/u][/b]", "creationdate": "2009-05-21T10:40:39-05:00", "id": 99274, "rating": 360, "commentid": 684065, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Xuven", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I logged in just to rate this comment up.  /salute", "creationdate": "2009-08-19T17:59:32-05:00", "id": 117254, "rating": 47, "commentid": 684065, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Skyywolf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Most of the married raiders I play with are couples where both the husband and wife play. I understand the comment about wife aggro was meant in jest, but it does hit upon an unfortunate tendency to look down on women in relation to gaming; a tendency which is very much NOT in jest, and is a very bad thing. The commenter could have said \"spouse aggro\" to the same effect, but chose to single out women. That says something... whether those up voting want to believe it or not.", "creationdate": "2013-01-11T16:40:45-06:00", "id": 621639, "rating": 3, "commentid": 684065, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MelTorefas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Mel, while I do understand your point about looking down on women in gaming (which is a very serious problem), I think it reads 'wife aggro' because Sif is Thorim's wife, not necessarily because of some misogynist feeling.", "creationdate": "2013-09-07T15:00:25-05:00", "id": 690232, "rating": 3, "commentid": 684065, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "valaraukarsbane", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 684361, "nreplies": 11, "sticky": 0, "user": "275081", "body": "Thorim? \r\n\r\nThe guy from the Storm Peaks quest?", "date": "2009-04-19T07:20:33-05:00", "rating": 119, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yup, but this is a corrupted Thorim. But now, at last, we can finally get our revenge... WHY THE **** DO YOU MAKE US FLY ALL OVER STORM PEAKS TO ASK SOME ICE GIANTS ABOUT YOUR HAMMER WHEN YOU COULD JUST FLY OVER THERE ON THAT GIANT DRAGON YOU GOT!", "creationdate": "2009-04-19T08:02:08-05:00", "id": 92340, "rating": 343, "commentid": 684361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Belse", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]WHY THE **** DO YOU MAKE US FLY ALL OVER STORM PEAKS TO ASK SOME ICE GIANTS ABOUT YOUR HAMMER WHEN YOU COULD JUST FLY OVER THERE ON THAT GIANT DRAGON [s]YOU GOT[/s] YOU MADE US GET FOR YOU![/quote]  FTFY.", "creationdate": "2009-06-19T22:35:09-05:00", "id": 104768, "rating": 62, "commentid": 684361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "IDrownFish", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]WHY THE **** DO YOU MAKE US FLY ALL OVER STORM PEAKS TO ASK SOME ICE GIANTS ABOUT YOUR HAMMER WHEN YOU COULD JUST FLY OVER THERE ON THAT GIANT DRAGON YOU GOT! [/quote] He has been disheartened for a really long time. Just do a favor for the old man and don't be a baby.", "creationdate": "2009-08-13T23:57:53-05:00", "id": 115985, "rating": 28, "commentid": 684361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "402216", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "But... He remembers us... In the mountains...", "creationdate": "2009-08-30T22:44:20-05:00", "id": 119378, "rating": 89, "commentid": 684361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Seriesh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Funny enough i've never done or visited the stormpeaks and yet he remembers me :D", "creationdate": "2009-09-20T14:36:19-05:00", "id": 123096, "rating": 44, "commentid": 684361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "88576", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 695306, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nethris", "body": "Extremely simple fight on 10-man.\n\nSplit your raid in half, one group (A) having one tank, one healer and 2 dps while the other one (B) has all the remaining players (Pref AoE dps).\n\nAt the first part (Jormungar + 4 captured soldiers) you can not fail, just tank the mobs and AoE them  down.\n\nAfter the mobs die, Thorim will stall babbling in confusion and Group A should pull the lever on the side of the arena and begin running through the gauntlet. The gauntlet itself is pretty simple, the only thing you need to watch out for is the big mob in the end of the first hallway, he will constantly \"explode\" the sides of the rooms which deal hefty damage if you stand on the wrong side. You can see which side will explode by looking at the mobs hands, which have fire coming out of them before the explosion comes. Careful while killing the mob too, he as a damage reflect buff. The other big mob before the end isnt much of a threat, he places a buff on one of the players fighting him which immobilizes and deals damage after a few seconds Oh, and while running to Thorim, in the last hall way, hug the sides unless you want to get stunned for ~20 seconds. Overall, its very easy and with 4 players, not a problem at all.\n\nWhile the gauntlet is done, adds will spawn in the arena where the remaining players are. Basically, its a big AoE zerg, where you target the sentinels first. Rogues are esp. good in the arena, tricks/dismanle/aoe works wonders.\n\nOnce the gauntlet is finished, Thorim jumps down and the \"real\" fight begins. AoE down the last adds and nuke down Thorim while avoiding the lightning coming out of the wall (Looks like multiple lightning bolts).\n\nOh, and if you fancy a laugh, try having ALL the players go in to the gauntlet. We didnt know what the %#/()= we were supposed to do and well, we got owned. Badly. Thorim didnt like it.", "date": "2009-04-26T18:19:10-05:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-26T18:20:05-05:00", 1, "Nethris"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 696937, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "d3nyd", "body": "This is a really fun and somewhat easy boss fight. On Normal mode, just be sure to stack 6 people (2 heals, a tank, 3 dps) in the arena and send the other four in the hallway. You'll probably have to take your time to NOT get the hard mode.", "date": "2009-04-27T23:50:24-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 697153, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "258417", "body": "Keypoints to avoid failure:\r\n\r\nHallway:\r\n1) Look at the big guy's hand at the end of the hall to see which side is going to get blown up. Yell in vent to signal it so nobody gets nuked.\r\n2) Near the end when you're at the top platform with Thorim, stay on the right edge of the wall or else you'll get stunned in a antimagic zone. In addition make sure to jump off the platform as soon as you can, as the platform will do a 3000/tick lightning aura.\r\n\r\nArena:\r\n1) Spread apart as his Hammer of Justice is \"aoe\" and will hit nearby targets.\r\n2) When lightning generator is on you, make sure to move away from the lightning orb that is generating it.\r\n\r\nGood luck have fun!", "date": "2009-04-28T05:11:16-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 697784, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "321573", "body": "can't believe this guy got beaten up by loken and his halls of llightning goons.", "date": "2009-04-28T15:53:28-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As Loken actually admits during the quest where they fight, Thorim is indeed stronger. However, Loken uses some \"weird, dark magic\" to capture Thorim.", "creationdate": "2009-05-01T08:28:59-05:00", "id": 95177, "rating": 52, "commentid": 697784, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Draenors", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "My guess is that Thorim couldn't remember to run out of the Lightning Nova.", "creationdate": "2009-05-13T09:13:11-05:00", "id": 97664, "rating": 167, "commentid": 697784, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "259842", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "actually, i think it's because loken drew thorim closer to ulduar, so that yogg-saron could corrupt him, hence the tentacle things that appear and the fact that hes a boss in ulduar...", "creationdate": "2009-06-24T09:13:15-05:00", "id": 412397, "rating": 0, "commentid": 697784, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "403107", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote Draenors]As Loken actually admits during the quest where they fight, Thorim is indeed stronger. However, Loken uses [s]some \"weird, dark magic\"[/s] [url=http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NaughtyTentacles]naughty tentacles[/url] to capture Thorim.[/quote]  Fix'd.", "creationdate": "2009-10-18T19:50:43-05:00", "id": 128088, "rating": 16, "commentid": 697784, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arathanar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 697838, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jahamakarahl", "body": "Thorim seams to have 2 types of Enrages. The first one is if you don't reach him within the 5 minutes. the other one is 4 minutes after he gets engaged and jumps down. Wowwiki states;\r\n\r\n[i]\"Once Thorim is activated, he will proceed with the fight, progressively gaining damage and attack speed as the fight goes on. This is a passive enrage timer, so speed is not a dependent requirement on his tank phase, but it is helpful.\"[/i]\r\n\r\nThis don't seam to be the case since I've personaly have experienced this enrage. He went enrage and did aproximatly 250-300k dmg per het on cloth.\r\n\r\nThis happened twice for us after 9 minutes after attacking Jormungar Behemoth. It could be that both time our other tanks died and the MT stood through hits all alone. Maby stacks gives him a berserk. In any case you should avoid this by nuking him down asap.", "date": "2009-04-28T16:52:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can see in his \"Abilities\" pane that he does infact have a typical 500/150 \"Berserk\"", "creationdate": "2009-04-30T17:55:53-05:00", "id": 403223, "rating": 0, "commentid": 697838, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "259842", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 701106, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Artea", "body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62446]Runic Mending[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62529]Runic Shield[/url] can be dispelled, so having a priest casting mass dispel on the adds that appear on the floor level every now and then can stop their heals and shields in their tracks.\r\n\r\nEdit:\r\n\r\nAnothing finding is that dispelling [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62526]Runic Detonation[/url] will cause it to immediately explode. Similar dispel results to grobbulus and his [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=28169]Mutating Injection[/url].", "date": "2009-05-01T08:46:30-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "They're also spellstealable too, at least the shield is.", "creationdate": "2009-05-03T08:17:39-05:00", "id": 95609, "rating": 10, "commentid": 701106, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Icecoldcoke", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-03T11:31:30-05:00", 1, "Artea"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 706478, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "335958", "body": "So far, I haven't seen any comments regarding his [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62130]\"Unbalancing Strike\"[/url].  This would concievably drop a tank into the critable/crushable state for 15 seconds.  Does this just require extra healing to manage, or is there a way to avoid the debuff?", "date": "2009-05-05T14:16:37-05:00", "rating": 25, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As was pointed out below by Alira, this is incorrect.  When afflicted with Unbalancing Strike, the tank may indeed become crushable.  This is because crush/crit mechanics are not actually based on your characters level, but rather on their defense skill vs. the enemy's weapon skill.  A raid boss (with 415 weapon skill at level 83) will crush any player who has less than or equal to 395 defense skill.  Therefore, unless your raid buffed defense skill is 596 or higher, you can be crushed when afflicted with Crushing Blow.  Note: I am assuming the crushable threshold is 20 defense skill.  For all", "creationdate": "2009-05-05T14:16:38-05:00", "id": 416711, "rating": 0, "commentid": 706478, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Larethorn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Have an offtank ready to taunt Thorim until the debuff wears off.", "creationdate": "2009-05-05T16:00:48-05:00", "id": 96160, "rating": 31, "commentid": 706478, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "159552", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "if i recall correctly, they changed the crush range to 4 levels above the target. the effective level for ? mobs is 83, thus, it's not that thorim's scripted to not crush, it's that he and his boss kindred cant.  this does not mean that he wont crit your ass out of the solar system when you have the debuff in question.. just means he wont crush it first.", "creationdate": "2009-06-09T15:08:53-05:00", "id": 102826, "rating": 18, "commentid": 706478, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "52997", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Someone tested this theory by using a Disgusting Oozeling (-20def aura) while having lvl 80 mobs attacking him, and he got crushing blows from those.. but not level 79 mobs. Additionally, if it did work as you say, then the adds from previous arena phase wouldn't be able to do crushing blows on the tank, but they can (as confirmed by wws's out there, and my own experience).", "creationdate": "2009-06-09T20:46:52-05:00", "id": 410117, "rating": 0, "commentid": 706478, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "baaboo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "25-man it is advisable to have an offtank pick it up for the duration, in 10-man however his damage is easily healed through in Naxx25 gear.", "creationdate": "2009-10-23T23:55:47-05:00", "id": 128872, "rating": 2, "commentid": 706478, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Malsherz", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 707756, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "90775", "body": "The Archivum Data Disc provides the following insights when the quest is turned in:\r\n\r\nAn external influence, under illusory guise of Thorim's deceased mate, Sif, has been detected.\r\nMental interference from this presence dangerously close to triggering partial memory damage.\r\nTactical analysis suggests approaching the arena from the front and splitting secondary force through a side passage at ground level.  This will maximize odds of reaching Thorim's outlook before mental domination by external presence is complete.", "date": "2009-05-06T16:35:56-05:00", "rating": 18, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 710470, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "223754", "body": "completed this now twice on 10 man on hard mode, here is what we had:\r\n\r\nprot warrior\r\nferal druid\r\n\r\nhunter (me)\r\nmoonkin\r\nwarlock\r\nwarlock\r\nshadow priest\r\nelemental shaman\r\n\r\nholy paladin\r\nholy priest\r\n\r\nin the gauntlet we had the warrior, holy priest, moonkin and one lock.  in the arena we went ffa nuking down anything that sawned.  with only 36k hp, the warbringers and evokers died in a blink of an eye, with the champions taking a little more attention.\r\n\r\nthe gauntlet team, needless to say, went as fast as they could, pulling non-stop through out, triggering hard mode with about 15-20 seconds to spare.\r\n\r\nonce thorim was in the arena, we spent about 10 seconds finishing off whatever add was left from the arena phase, debuffed the boss and popped heroism.\r\n\r\neven with thorim's lack of debuff now, tank healing is not THAT hard, until he gets to about 4-5 stacks of his buff.  at that stage, tanks and healers started rotating cooldowns to make life easier, and the elemental shaman helped out raid healing at this point as well.\r\n\r\nthings to note about sif joining the battle:\r\n1. she uses frost nova, usually not an issue, but if you are caught in an incoming lighting charge, let the healers know you're in trouble for a dispell.\r\n2.  frost bolt volley.  its really just an irritant, and the dmg from it is easily healed by judgement of light if you're lucky enough to have it.\r\n3. blizzard.  this will pull people down pretty fast.  it has, at least it seemed to me, a stringer slowing effect than other blizzards, and obviously cant be dispelled.  it moves round the room like the one from shade of aran, and like with that blizzard, if you get caught in it, either at the start of it or later, the fastest way out is moving towards the centre of the room or walking through it asgainst the movement.\r\n4. at 4-5 buffs thorims chain lightning will start to one shot people after 2 jumps.  speading it very important here.\r\n\r\ngood luck to those that try this, hope this info helped :)", "date": "2009-05-09T09:27:33-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 716199, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sangnoir", "body": "The Unbalancing strike (reducing tanks def by 200) cannot be dodged, parried or blocked (but can miss). \r\n\r\nTanks will usually not survive more than two hits while under the effect of the strike, as it reduces dodge,block and parry chance as well as lifting the crit chance against the tank. The strike itself does significant dmg.\r\n\r\nSo for any second tank: keep your eye on the mts unitframe or be prepared when any bossmod anounces the tank being under the effect of unbalancing strike and immidiately hit the taunt button and be prepared for resist/miss. A wasted second means much likely the death of your tank.\r\n\r\nActivate Trinkets to help your healers. \r\n\r\nAs the buff on thorim stacks, tanks should consider using shield-wall-like abilities.", "date": "2009-05-14T16:40:21-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Unbalancing strike can also be intervened by a warrior with careful timing, causing the intervening warrior to get the debuff, instead of the current tank.  On our 25-man last night both myself and the other prot warrior would rotate intervenes when DBM said the cooldown on the strike was ready. Both warriors intervened the druid tank who tanked Thorim for the whole fight, catching 75% of the unbalancing strikes.", "creationdate": "2009-05-19T11:53:31-05:00", "id": 98877, "rating": 5, "commentid": 716199, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "368363", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Why would defense rating loss even remotely matter for a druid tank?", "creationdate": "2009-05-28T05:22:40-05:00", "id": 408204, "rating": 0, "commentid": 716199, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Stillwater", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Druids while they don't need def rating from gear is only because they get 6% reduced crit from talents, if their base 400 def skill gets lowered well there's gonna be trouble,", "creationdate": "2009-05-28T19:35:39-05:00", "id": 408310, "rating": 1, "commentid": 716199, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tharrix", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "However, with 624 resilience, a druid tank will remain uncrittable. The defense loss will also cause a druid to lose about 8% avoidance, compared to 25% avoidance for a plate tank.", "creationdate": "2009-06-20T07:49:03-05:00", "id": 411674, "rating": 1, "commentid": 716199, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "34089", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 716689, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "262888", "body": "The most reliable and easy way to do 25man is to have\r\n1 tank, 1 healer,1 hunter, 2 mages and 1-2 more dps in gauntlet. This will leave arena group with 5-6 healers and a lot of dps to handle arena adds.\r\nMages should sheep healer and 2nd small add. So tank will not recieve much damage and 1 healer will be enough for gauntlet fight.\r\nSecond big guy will spawn mobs all the time untill you engage him.\r\nSheep 2, kill another 2 starting from healer and let hunter misdirect big guy to tank before he spawn any additional mobs. Burn you CDs to kill 3 adds and kill big guy.\r\n\r\nOn 10man fight is really easy. 6ppl on arena, 4 ppl on gauntlet and just aoe all adds down.", "date": "2009-05-15T04:50:57-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-15T04:52:34-05:00", 1, "262888"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 717425, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "hellshadow", "body": "I would personally like to see some extracted sound files for this fight, if possible.", "date": "2009-05-15T21:07:30-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 723505, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "86556", "body": "A few words of help for hardmode attempts:\r\n\r\nSif is more or less only annoying, her damage is not too hard to outheal but the things you should keep in mind are the slows and roots she does, after blinking she will wait around 2-3 seconds to do a frostnova, its actually possible to move out before she does it even if she blinks on you. The big danger is getting into the charged sectors cause of roots/slows.\r\n\r\nThe 'timer' we considered helpfull for this fight is with the stacks, we estimated his death around 10 stacks of the selfbuff, but it's easy for your tanks to do die before this. We decided just to let the tanks and healers use their cooldown somewhat planned when the stacks hit 7+. So try to get 10% health of him for before each stack.\r\n\r\nBe prepared for a tank to die at 9+ stacks just keep nuking and don't panic, you can kite him around for a long while before you wipe.\r\n\r\nOne more thing, note that with the stacking selfbuff he also increases his nature dmg and this adds up quite much. Never stand in the charged sectors and avoid chaining the chain lightning especially at the last part of the fight.\r\n\r\nOur setup was: Warrior (tank), Deathknight (tank), Druid (healer), Priest (healer-holy), hunter, mage, warlock, shaman (elem), rogue and priest (shadow).\r\n\r\nWasn't a very hard hard-mode, took us about 2 hours. Changing to 2 instead of 3 healers made our difference.", "date": "2009-05-21T17:10:05-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
