{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 725617, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Elennoko", "body": "I was surprised myself...Ah well, here ya go!\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Berserk01.wav\")\n[b]My patience has reached its limit! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Defeated01.wav\")\n[b]Stay your arms! I yield! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_HardEpi01.wav\")\n[b]You! Fiend! You are not my beloved! Be gone! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_HardEpi02.wav\")\n[b]Behold the hand behind all the evil that has befallen Ulduar! Left my kingdom in ruins, corrupted my brother and slain my wife! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_HardEpi03.wav\")\n[b]And now it falls to you, champions, to avenge us all! The task before you is great, but I will lend you my aid as I am able. You must prevail! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_JumpDown01.wav\")\n[b]Impertinent whelps! You dare challenge me atop my pedestal! I will crush you myself! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Misc01.wav\")\n[b]Behold the power of the storms and despair! \n[/b]\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Misc02.wav\")\n[b]Do not hold back! Destroy them! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Misc03.wav\")\n[b]Have you begun to regret your intrusion? [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_NormEpi01.wav\")\n[b]I feel as though I am awakening from a nightmare, but the shadows in this place yet linger. [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_NormEpi02.wav\")\n[b]Sif... was Sif here? Impossible! She died by my brother's hand. A dark nightmare indeed. [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_NormEpi03.wav\")\n[b]I need time to reflect. I will aid your cause if you should require it. I owe you at least that much. Farewell. [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_P1Wipe01.wav\")\n[b]Failures! Weaklings! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Slay01.wav\")\n[b]Can't you at least put up a fight! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Slay02.wav\")\n[b]Pathetic! [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Start01.wav\")\n[b]Interlopers! You mortals who dare to interfere with my sport will pay... Wait--you...\n[/b]\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_Start02.wav\")\n[b]I remember you... In the mountains... But you... what is this? Where am-- [/b]\n\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Thorim\\\\UR_Thorim_YSHelp01.wav\")\n[b]Golganneth, lend me your strengh! Grant my mortal allies the power of thunder![/b]", "date": "2009-05-23T23:21:51-05:00", "rating": 56, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-06-19T21:20:48-05:00", 1, "Elennoko"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 736253, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "261770", "body": "Some minutes ago I tanked him on hard (U25) from 100 to 1 with my Paly (feral taunted 3 times to be second in aggro for safety) and I'm still trembling.\n\nDefinitly a palyboss from what I can say now .. capped block takes 8-10% of his whitedamage off the scale and when he starts to throw blows each 0.3 seconds this pays of big.\n\nNeed second tankCD. Gief!", "date": "2009-06-03T15:59:20-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-06-03T16:02:15-05:00", 1, "261770"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 736809, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "238144", "body": "I'm surprised no one has mentioned this before, but \"Thorim\" appears to be based on the old god \"Thor\" from nordic mythology, just like Freya is.\r\n\r\nThor was the god of thunder in norse mythology. He had Mjolnir, his magical hammer which would return to him every time he threw it. Thorim reflects this with his Stormhammer ability.\r\n\r\nLikewise, Thor's wife was named Sif, just like Thorim's wife.", "date": "2009-06-04T07:11:52-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "so is Loken (loki) , Hodir (Odin) and Mimiron (Mimir). Skadi in UP. mob names and the npc cities in storm peak /icecrown The whole expansion is based on norse mythology.", "creationdate": "2009-06-30T02:36:46-05:00", "id": 106853, "rating": 21, "commentid": 736809, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jell", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "All the four keepers refer to Gods of the Norse mythology, known as: Tor, Freja, Mimer and Oden (Thorim, Freya, Mimiron, Hodir)", "creationdate": "2009-08-06T17:21:31-05:00", "id": 418991, "rating": 0, "commentid": 736809, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kepsen", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "so is Loken (loki) , Hodir (Odin) and Mimiron (Mimir). Skadi in UP. mob names and the npc cities in storm peak /icecrown The whole expansion is based on norse mythology.  Actually, Hodir is more likely a reference to Hodr, the blind son of Odin who killed his brother Baldr in a game set up by Loki :o", "creationdate": "2009-10-10T17:12:53-05:00", "id": 126764, "rating": 10, "commentid": 736809, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "385742", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "So.....Hodir has a brother named Baldy that was killed? Hope to see him in Icecrown.", "creationdate": "2010-01-15T18:00:43-06:00", "id": 143504, "rating": 3, "commentid": 736809, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "520501", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Correct, Hodr shot an arrow imbued with mistletoe at Baldr, because he was immune from everything but mistletoe.", "creationdate": "2010-02-14T14:11:06-06:00", "id": 149101, "rating": 1, "commentid": 736809, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "545509", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 737748, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "evermore", "body": "A large portion of Northrend is based on norse mythology and viking culture. Not only Thorim and Freya, but Hodir as well. In addition, most of the Howling Fjord and large portions of Icecrown, including the Utgarde instances.", "date": "2009-06-05T06:05:16-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 743992, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Okacz", "body": "Many people are suprised , that they find Thorim in Ulduar, after doing quests for him. In fact Thorim was cheated by Loken. He murered Thorim's wife, Sif, and told him, that it was Ice Giands work. Thorim turned against his allies and felt in a long depression. Thats why players find him alone, away from the entire world.\r\nThorim had been corrupted by Yogg-Saron. The Old God made an illusion of Thorim's wife, Sif, to keep him corrupted in Ulduar. When he engages, he dont want  to attack players at first, cuz he reminds, that they helped him. It is Sif who tells him to attack. \r\nAfter dealing with him the \"curse\" is broken and Torim is friendly again. He can help you then in Yogg-Saron fight.", "date": "2009-06-11T16:14:42-05:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 744817, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kaylthas", "body": "He looked better with the original model...\r\n\r\nThis one looks like a fat old man, nothing like a god of thunder.", "date": "2009-06-12T14:55:05-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 751575, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Finbarr", "body": "After all we did for him!\r\nAfter we got him off his lazy butt,\r\nReforged alliances with the frost giants for him, \r\nand [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=13009]fixed his armor[/url],\r\n[i]THIS[/i] is how he repays us?\r\nBy getting with your buddies Freya, Hodir, and Mimiron,\r\nand trying to beat us to death?\r\n/huff\r\n\r\n\r\n(Note, this was sarcasm.)", "date": "2009-06-19T16:29:57-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Technically, it's YOUR fault (as the player) that Thorim was captured in the first place; as \"Lok'lira the Crone\" (the female Vrykul in the mines who starts the Thorim Quest Chain and also gives you the female Vrykul illusion buff) is actually Loken in disguise manipulating you to \"help\" Thorim confront Loken in his Temple near Ulduar so that Yogg-Saron could ensnare him.", "creationdate": "2009-06-29T13:51:39-05:00", "id": 106738, "rating": 27, "commentid": 751575, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mooshimanx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "probably another connection to loki; who often shapeshifted in the myths", "creationdate": "2010-08-23T01:56:32-05:00", "id": 178762, "rating": 0, "commentid": 751575, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nordur", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 753770, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "337736", "body": "i cant believe this guy!  he wasted my life flying all around storm peaks on a slow skeleton, making me do all these nice things for him.  AND NOW HE WNATS TO KILL ME?  I CANT BELIEVE HIM.", "date": "2009-06-21T13:43:56-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 764264, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Alira", "body": "Now there's one thing about the unbalancing strikes that people fail to mention, it is correct that it reduces your defense skill by 200. It was asked if this made the tank vulnerable to crushing blows, and was stated it does not. This is indeed incorrect!\r\n\r\nThe level threshold for crushing blows is 4 levels, but this is calculated by asumin a level 83 mob has a weapon skill of 415 (83*5) and a level 80 player has 400 (a tank at least 540) defense. A difference in attackers weapon skill and defenders defense skill of 20 is required in order to calculate crushing blows into the combat rolls.\r\n\r\nNow consider the tank having his defense lowered by 200, leaving Thorim with 415 weapon skill and the tank with 340 (assuming he is not over-def'ing his crit immunity (some are, some don't)) This is a difference of 75.. 75 > 20 and thus you will be subject to crushing blows while under the effect of unbalancing strikes.\r\n\r\nI as a protection Paladin recorded a crushing blow upon myself during an attempt last week, though did not get  a screenshot of this happening, but I can assure you that while under the effect of Unbalancing Strikes, Crushing Blows is a factor to be dealt with.", "date": "2009-07-01T04:36:53-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "no unbalancing strike will not make you crushable. to be crushed the attacker needs have 20 or more weapon skill above your BASE defense, for level 80 this is 400, so only mobs with a base weapon skill of 420 can crush a tank, as said above, unbalancing strike will make you critable.  if indeed you could be crushed then people wouldn't be here asking if you could be, as the chance to be crushed is 2% per skill difference - 20%, in your example the difference is 75 skill points, this means there is a 135% chance to be crushed. now with this i can just about guarantee you cant be crushed, as hav", "creationdate": "2009-07-01T04:36:54-05:00", "id": 424652, "rating": 2, "commentid": 764264, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pherexian", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 767503, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Iceleaf", "body": "If you are having clothies or problems with the arena group dying fast because adds aggro you instantly theres one mechanic that should help with this. One user in Elitist Jerks noted that person who is closest to Thorim during arena gets instant aggro of the adds. So if you are healer or otherwise \"squishy\" dont go past your tank and you should do fine.\n\nEdit: Naturally powergain aggro, heal aggros still apply.", "date": "2009-07-04T10:24:46-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "One observation to add to this - I am a healer one of the aforementioned \"squishies\". I did notice that this was the case on Thorim. Most of the mobs will run right passed you... however, you can still pull aggro from healing before the mob gets anywhere near the tank. If the tank is aware of this they can pull this usually single mob to them without interruption. Often times it's a caster mob that was trailing behind to cast.", "creationdate": "2009-07-17T13:42:50-05:00", "id": 110283, "rating": 2, "commentid": 767503, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "395821", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-03-30T12:20:18-05:00", 1, "Iceleaf"]}
