{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 1767643, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "AventuraPL", "body": "Soloed [achievement=3176] as an Affli Warlock with Voidlord.\r\n\r\n[b]Tactic:[/b]\r\nIt is impossible to fight against Thorim in Normal Mode, because he resets. The only way is to kill him by activating his Hard Mode. Phase 1 (reaching Thorim) is the most difficult part of the fight. Voidlord should be set to passive (you command it manually). Kill all the adds in the arena, open the gate by using the lever, run into the corridor where you pull Runic Colossus (use Burning Rush and Dark Regeneration!) and quickly return to the arena (keep the big add alive). Place your Demonic Portal just past the gate, return to the arena and wait for reset. Kill all the adds in the arena except Runic Colossus and one additional mob. Teleport past the gate, resummon Voidlord and kill Runic Colossus. Keep the add from the arena alive as you kill the rest enemies on your way to Thorim. When you are near Thorim, kill the add from the arena and wait for Thorim to do his roleplay until Sif spawns. If you enter earlier, you fail... If you wait too much, you fail too... Do not bother counter of Hard Mode in the DBM, because it counts the time from the first pull, rather than the reset. When you jump down, do not forget to resummon Voidlord. Now defeat Thorim while avoiding Lightning Charge. Good Luck and Have Fun!\r\n\r\n[b]Video:[/b]\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MCyzkHCs3YQ", "date": "2012-11-25T10:50:02-06:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I was able to do something similar as a Monk by placing a Transcendence point past the gate. The hardest part is timing Thorim's activation until after Sif's line.", "creationdate": "2012-11-25T19:19:28-06:00", "id": 603044, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1767643, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "203799", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I was really stuck until I watched this vid, it shows exactly where to kill the last mob, how longo wait and when to jump.", "creationdate": "2014-05-04T22:47:26-05:00", "id": 744209, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1767643, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zyrinx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 1775573, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "488606", "body": "As of 12/4/12 this appears to have been hotfixed to reset differently.\r\n\r\nAs a hunter I left my pet in the arena, using the talent to gain run speed after disengage + rocket jump + engineering run speed boost I could not beat the reset and lightning ball. \r\n\r\nIt now seems to reset when you reach bow/spell range of the first miniboss and not as a timer. \r\n\r\nWhy blizzard fixes some bosses to be easier to solo while fixing others to make it impossible..I am not sure. Please downrate if it works for you, but I've tried seven times now and each time it reset before I could tag the golem.", "date": "2012-12-04T17:22:23-06:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 1777873, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "kpk02", "body": "It's still possible to solo as of 2 days ago. I managed to do it as a DK as follows:\r\n\r\nWhen you first enter the arena, make note of where the dwarf in the back (under Thorim's platform) is.. for later reference.\r\n\r\nKill off everything on the arena floor except one mob.  Run over by the switch, kill the mob and hit the switch to open the gate. \r\n\r\nRun through and just past halfway to the big mob, hit all of your speed buffs, tag the big guy, and get your butt back out into the arena before the spark of doom catches you.  I normally hit my speed buffs when Thorim says \"Failures! All of you!\" or something like that.  That phrase tells you he's initiating the raid wipe spark ball.\r\n\r\nOnce back out in the arena, wait for the big guy to make it back out. He consistently would punt me just about as soon as he reached me.  I'd wait a couple of seconds then drop death and decay around where that original dwarf in the back stays.  Then I'd wait a couple seconds and quickly get back into the tunnel before the gate closes. \r\n\r\nThe gate will close and the mobs in the arena will respawn. You should still have the big guy alive at this point. My DnD tagged the mobs in the arena and they ran through the gate to me. Mark one of the arena mobs to keep alive. I usually marked the one with 500k+ health.  Go ahead and kill the big guy and it will open the door at the end of the hall.\r\n\r\nFrom this point on, kill everything except the mob you marked.  This is because Thorim doesn't trigger phase 2 until all of the arena mobs are dead.. and that marked mob is the last remaining arena mob. \r\n\r\nOnce you get through the second door go out to the middle area of the room and kill off the marked mob.  Thorim will start talking.. and here timing is critical.  You need to hit Thorim and jump off down to the arena.. but you have to do it after Sif spawns but before Thorim triggers a reset (spark ball).\r\n\r\nSorry not the best explanation but here are the key parts:\r\n\r\n1. You need to drag the big guy guarding the first door back out into the arena before the fight resets.\r\n2. You need to be back in the tunnel before the reset hits and have aggro'd the arena stuff that respawns so it follows you into the tunnel after the gate is closed.\r\n3. You need to keep one of the arena mobs alive until ready to trigger Phase 2\r\n4. You need to trigger phase 2 while close enough to thorim so you can both hit him and jump down immediately as Sif spawns.", "date": "2012-12-08T17:04:59-06:00", "rating": 32, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is the best time to get a fuel leak while using nitro boosts (before spark'o'death gets you).", "creationdate": "2013-04-29T08:29:15-05:00", "id": 654756, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1777873, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "nealj121", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Great guide, but I'm stuck on key part 4, pulling him down before the spark spawns. It seems to me that the spark spawns before Sif, and that there's no way to change that.", "creationdate": "2013-08-26T14:36:56-05:00", "id": 687593, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1777873, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Teerai", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Gah - so frustrating. Most of the time I can get up there with my marked arena mob, but from there nothing seems to actually start the fight as described. Killing the marked mob doesn't seem to spawn Sif; Thorim just jumps down and isnt attackable.", "creationdate": "2014-05-04T20:26:17-05:00", "id": 744199, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1777873, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zyrinx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Does anyone know if this is an exploit? I was doing a vid on how to do it, and I just wanna make sure", "creationdate": "2014-05-28T19:50:47-05:00", "id": 748428, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1777873, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Gelli", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 1779689, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chakra", "body": "[quote]By kpk02 (108 \u2013 1) 2 days ago (Patch 5.1.0)\n\nIt's still possible to solo as of 2 days ago. I managed to do it as a DK as follows:\n\nWhen you first enter the arena, make note of where the dwarf in the back (under Thorim's platform) is.. for later reference.\n\nKill off everything on the arena floor except one mob. Run over by the switch, kill the mob and hit the switch to open the gate.\n\nRun through and just past halfway to the big mob, hit all of your speed buffs, tag the big guy, and get your butt back out into the arena before the spark of doom catches you. I normally hit my speed buffs when Thorim says \"Failures! All of you!\" or something like that. That phrase tells you he's initiating the raid wipe spark ball.\n\nOnce back out in the arena, wait for the big guy to make it back out. He consistently would punt me just about as soon as he reached me. I'd wait a couple of seconds then drop death and decay around where that original dwarf in the back stays. Then I'd wait a couple seconds and quickly get back into the tunnel before the gate closes.\n\nThe gate will close and the mobs in the arena will respawn. You should still have the big guy alive at this point. My DnD tagged the mobs in the arena and they ran through the gate to me. Mark one of the arena mobs to keep alive. I usually marked the one with 500k+ health. Go ahead and kill the big guy and it will open the door at the end of the hall.\n\nFrom this point on, kill everything except the mob you marked. This is because Thorim doesn't trigger phase 2 until all of the arena mobs are dead.. and that marked mob is the last remaining arena mob.\n\nOnce you get through the second door go out to the middle area of the room and kill off the marked mob. Thorim will start talking.. and here timing is critical. You need to hit Thorim and jump off down to the arena.. but you have to do it after Sif spawns but before Thorim triggers a reset (spark ball).\n\nSorry not the best explanation but here are the key parts:\n\n1. You need to drag the big guy guarding the first door back out into the arena before the fight resets.\n2. You need to be back in the tunnel before the reset hits and have aggro'd the arena stuff that respawns so it follows you into the tunnel after the gate is closed.\n3. You need to keep one of the arena mobs alive until ready to trigger Phase 2\n4. You need to trigger phase 2 while close enough to thorim so you can both hit him and jump down immediately as Sif spawns.[/quote]\n\nAwesome guide. It helped me alot. I had to figure out some things for myself which i will share with the rest.\n\nYou MUST have the talent Death Siphon for the 40 yard range to tag the first big guy.\nYou MUST have Death's Advance and run in Unholy Presence. (Or a Swiftness Potion).\n\nHit the switch and use Death's Advance right away. Use Icebound Fortitude when you aggro the dwarves to avoid their stun. Death Siphon the big guy and immediatly turn around. The small ones will despawn.\n\nStand on the stairs tanking the big guy.\n\nUse this macro exactly when the big ball of lightning disappear:\n\n/sw\n/click StopwatchResetButton\n/click StopwatchPlayPauseButton\n\nWait exactly 15 seconds and drop Death and Decay. It is absolutely cruicial that you drop it to aggro ALL mobs in the arena. Sometimes they all don't come as a pack, so place your DnD with care.\n\nKill everyone but the Iron Dwarf from the arena up until you're in front of Thorim. Kill him, wait for Sif to spawn and immediatly Death Coil Thorim and jump down.\n\nThis should do it.", "date": "2012-12-11T15:41:23-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-12T17:57:23-06:00", 1, "Chakra"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 1782740, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Olesril", "body": "Can you solo as a druid?\r\n[b]YES[/b]\r\n\r\nHow?\r\n[b]Carefully[/b]\r\n\r\n[ol]\r\n[li]Guardian Spec[/li]\r\n[ol]\r\n[li]Force of Nature[/li]\r\n[ol]\r\n[li]Near perfect timing[/li]\r\n[/ol]\r\nStart of just like everyone else does (kill arena adds)\r\nOpen gate and dash to last [b]BIG[/b] guy FF and run out.\r\nSit in the middle of the arena.\r\n\r\nThis is the tricky part.\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Dont Attack Him[/li]\r\n[li]Timing is key[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\nAfter lightning bolt goes through gauntlet and the big guy passes the gate you have ~ 15 seconds to get this part down.[ol]\r\n[li]Wait about 8 seconds.[/li]\r\n[li]Drop Force of Nature in the middle of the ring (guardian spec grants them a taunt)[/li]\r\n[li]Make sure the Big guy is attacking your trees.[/li]\r\n[li]Feral charge back into the gauntlet and wait.[/li]\r\n[/ol]\r\n\r\nIf done corectly the Arena adds will have spawned and started attacking your little trees. Once your trees die they will come to you. \r\n\r\nFinish as the rest of the Classes do.", "date": "2012-12-16T20:40:39-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I love you so much!", "creationdate": "2014-07-25T07:04:19-05:00", "id": 759962, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1782740, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1259867", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
