{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 1819065, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MarkusF", "body": "I finally managed to do it as a hunter. Hardest part was getting the healer to agro me. I ended up putting pet passive in center, and fire trap exactely where this dwarf would spawn. That would pull them all.\r\n\r\nThree general tips:\r\n\r\n1) Darkwater Potion. Did not see it mentioned, but it is a 70% runspeed buf for all. Together with aspect of cheeta, I managed to easily make the run in and back. So any other speed buf your class/race might have, together with this easily optainable potion should solve your speed issues.\r\n\r\nEmpty the AH or create a pile before you go though, as you don't want to have to go back after a few failed attempts. Just get a huge stack with you.\r\n\r\n2) When you fail, allow the encounter to FULLY reset else you'll end up with multiple phases mixed. Hilarious sometimes, but will not allow you to get it. I have had two sparks with a few seconds fireed to me, had a spark with gate that had reclosed on me, mobs that resetted while fighting, the big guy despawn, or myself locked inside the gate area with all the mobs on evade, etc.\r\n\r\n3) Oh, and don't be an idiot like me and wait for Sif to spawn. I failed to read properly and failed 4 times in a row before I understood that. After spawn don't wait too long though else you will not be able to miss the spark.", "date": "2013-02-27T21:29:20-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-02-27T21:31:04-06:00", 1, "MarkusF"]}
