{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 1871049, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "DoomDR", "body": "Soloable as of 5.3 as an Arms Warrior. I used the strat as kpk202 said. However, I used nitro boots to aggro the big guy at the end of the hallway before the stairs and used heroic leap to get away from them using the 4pc PvP set. \r\n\r\nI then threw my demoralizing banner into the middle of the room to aggro them like a DND or Hammer would. The rest of it I followed kpk202's strat and it worked flawlessly.", "date": "2013-06-27T00:57:37-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 1885736, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Thalloren", "body": "Soloed as an ilvl 509 Frost Mage.\n\nI used the same strategy as kpk02, the Death Knight above. Thorim himself isn't particularly hard, as long as you pop the usual CDs such as Time Warp and Mirror Image. Getting to fight Thorim by yourself is the hard part, as the mechanics are meant to keep you from soloing him.\n\nTo override the mechanics: Kill all the starting arena mobs. Be ready to pull the lever to the gate [i]as soon as Thorim begins to speak[/i]. If you wait too long, the stormforged dwarves who begin to attack you will keep interrupting your attempts. Once you open the gate, immediately run down and around the corner toward the giant mob at the far end. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=1953]Blink[/url] as soon as you round the corner, then use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=108978]Alter Time[/url] around the center of the circular room. Keep running toward the giant mob and throw an [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=131080]Ice Lance[/url] at him. If you timed it right, Alter Time will pull you back right after you pull the big mob. He should stay aggroed on you. Turn around and run back toward the gate, casting [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=108843]Blazing Speed[/url] immediately. Blink should come off of cooldown once you turn the corner; use it again to get to the gate. You will need ALL of these spells to get out of the gate before the insta-kill spark reaches you. If you are missing any of these, you [i]may[/i] be able to replace it with a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=2459]Swiftness Potion[/url], but I haven't tested that.\n\nOnce you have pulled the giant mob back through the gate, resummon your Water Elemental (it should have been killed by the spark) and [i]make it STAY[/i] in the middle of the room. Also set it to passive. It must NOT kill the giant mob before the fight resets, which is indicated by the gate closing and the arena mobs respawning. [b]You MUST be inside the gate when it closes, NOT in the arena.[/b] Now you can kill the giant mob. This will open the door at the end of the hallway, allowing you to reach Thorim.\n\nFrom here, you will need to kill the arena mobs to actually restart the fight. But, since you're on the opposite side of the gate from them, you cannot pull them yourself. This is why you placed your elemental on the far side. Click on any of the mobs and have your elemental begin attacking it. Once it pulls aggro, resummoning it inside the gate next to you [i]should[/i] pull all the arena mobs through the gate to you. (This has worked every time I tried it, even when only one mob was attacked. I assume they will always all come together.) Now, kill [b]all but one[/b] of the arena mobs. Leaving the captain alive is safe, because he has the most health and you're least likely to kill him on accident. Also, [b]set your elemental to passive again[/b] so it doesn't accidentally kill the last arena mob and start the fight too early.\n\nNow you need to run to the end of the tunnel and kill the other big mob at the top of the stairs to open the second door. Do not kill the remaining arena mob until you are in the larger room where you can see Thorim.\n\nKill the arena mob. Thorim will start talking. Get close to him, [b]but not too close[/b] or he will jump down to the floor before you can aggro him, then despawn. I'm not sure exactly where the line is; there's a line between two different kinds of flooring pretty close to him, and it might be that, but you can be somewhat cautious here.\n\nThe final part is a bit tricky. Sif will appear and start talking to him. This is when Thorim becomes a \"valid target.\" Now you can attack him and jump down to the floor, actually beginning the fight. But this is also about when he will summon the giant spark of death, which appears almost exactly where you're standing. You need to know about how long his speech takes, and start running toward him right when Sif appears. Hit him with an Ice Lance as you run by, then jump down to the floor. If all goes well, you will have done some damage to him and not died yourself. That's all you need; you should be able to fight him normally now. Like I said, he's fairly easy; certainly easier than a number of the other bosses I've soloed from Ulduar and Icecrown. Good luck!\n\nThis strategy should work for any class that is both fast enough to pull the big mob at the end of the hallway, and has a way of damaging the arena mobs through the gate once they respawn.\n\n[b]TL;DR:\n- Open the gate, pull the giant mob at the end of the hall. Get out before giant spark of death kills you.\n- Pull arena mobs through gate with your elemental once fight resets. Leave one alive until you reach the room right before Thorim.\n- Kill remaining arena mob. Tag Thorim when Sif appears, then jump to the floor before giant spark of death appears.\n- Kill Thorim.[/b]", "date": "2013-08-09T21:30:27-05:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well, not every class got a pet to stay in the arena...", "creationdate": "2014-04-26T02:13:50-05:00", "id": 742575, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1885736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Volvic", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I just used this method as an Elemental Shaman (no pet used since the Ele's despawn if you get too far. A warlock mentioned a roughly 36 second timer between \"FAILURES!\" and respawn, so I counted...dropped a magma totem near the Iron Dwarf healer and timed my Earthquake that it would hit the other NPC's while still giving me enough time to get back inside the gate. After that, I ran through killed the mobs one by one, and killed the final arena mob last, tagged Thorim, jumped down, won fight. No help, no pet, just solo.", "creationdate": "2014-05-14T13:05:16-05:00", "id": 745871, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1885736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "vfarkill", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-08-09T21:35:53-05:00", 2, "Thalloren"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 1890559, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "hausmaus", "body": "502 Ret pally, also following Kpk502's advice.  I thought I'd share a couple details for other pallies:\r\n\r\nAfter you kill the initial set of arena mobs and go into the hallway, you'll need to sprint in, tag the big guy, and sprint out, as stated.  For this, I found [spell=26023] to be the talent of choice.  You will also need a [item=2459], and [spell=642].\r\n\r\nThe trick is timing Divine Shield.  Make sure you have full Holy Power after killing the last mob.  As you enter the hallway, refresh Sacred Shield.  The mobs in the hallway stun, so you need DS to get past them, but you want to rely on SS and avoidance for at least a GCD after they start attacking.  Then you pop Divine Shield.  Judge the big mob the instant you can (and make sure it goes off!), then immediately turn and hit the potion.\r\n\r\nThe reason for waiting on the potion is that otherwise, you'll be charging into mobs when the shield fades, rather than away, and also to avoid any overshoot as you're running towards the big guy.  I found that if you are off by a single step or a fraction of a second with DS, you will get stunned.\r\n\r\nFor tagging the second wave of arena mobs when the encounter resets, you will of course need Light's Hammer.  You need to aim this near the rim of that golden disc on the ground, closer to Thorim, to ensure that it hits all the mobs.  It's annoyingly easy to miss one.\r\n\r\nThen get back in the tunnel, kill the big guy, blitz the tunnel mobs, mark the Captain when the arena mobs catch up to you, and then kill them all except the Captain.  You need to kill the Captain closeish to Thorim, past the midpoint of that large tan circle in the ground before him.  The line you have to watch out for is the first row of blue bricks in the ground right before his little platform.  If you step on that last row of blue bricks, he'll jump down and reset.  If you kill the Captain too far away, Sif won't appear.  You want to be in that huge beige disc, kill the Captain, and then wait until he becomes attackable to tag him and jump down.\r\n\r\nAnd then, after a few hours, a stack of potions, and hundreds in repairs, you'll have a dagger, mail belt, and the wrong shoulders to show for it.  At least that was my magnificient haul.\r\n\r\nThis thing can bug out enough ways to really make you crazy.  Just keep at it and you will get it, it is entirely about timing.\r\n\r\nGood luck!", "date": "2013-08-27T00:10:05-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "515 ret pally, able to solo with this strat (also a good video of it here: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ljab7FUxRwU.) Had much the same luck in repairs and loot (sigh)", "creationdate": "2013-10-19T16:40:52-05:00", "id": 702408, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1890559, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sherrasama", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 1892767, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "hoofio", "body": "Don't suppose anyone knows of a trinket or somesuch for aggroing the reset mobs that can be farmed for those classes that have no DnD, mocking banner etc?\r\n\r\nIronically, the only trink I think will do the job is [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=46312][/url] that drops from Yogg that I can't get to solo...\r\n\r\nthanks!", "date": "2013-09-04T05:32:26-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If you are trying to pull groups of mobs, you might want to try Battle Horn. It is a drop from Blackhoof in Valley of the Four Winds in Pandaria or from the Ordon Candlekeepers on Timeless Isle in Pandaria. It attracts enemies within 40 yards with a 2 minute cooldown.", "creationdate": "2014-01-05T18:35:41-06:00", "id": 719534, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1892767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "sakera", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Battle Horn doesn't work. Just tried it.", "creationdate": "2014-01-20T18:21:59-06:00", "id": 723091, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1892767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "anselmoo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "http://www.wowhead.com/item=21579 ?", "creationdate": "2014-07-21T04:01:37-05:00", "id": 758973, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1892767, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "khrrull", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
