{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 1923070, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "mootrone", "body": "So is this strat busted cause I been trying all night pew pew one arena mob near Thorim, he does not reset as he had last week... stood there 10min, no intro dialogue.", "date": "2013-12-03T00:46:29-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "ok this does still work as hunter at least, your pet gets bugged out to stay in the arena, so after you kill the arena mob near thorim he will reset, & soon as \"where am --\" & sith starts talking & he gets his 90% debuff, pew pew & jump down.", "creationdate": "2013-12-03T01:14:17-06:00", "id": 712160, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1923070, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mootrone", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-12-03T00:50:52-06:00", 1, "mootrone"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 1929725, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "darkoath", "body": "As of 12/28/13, this is still soloable per the strategy previously mentioned. I did it with my destro warlock and I sac'd my demon, so it's not important to have a pet out. It is worth mentioning that from the time Thorim says his \"failure\" speech to the time the mobs respawn and the gate closes, approximately [b]36 seconds has elapsed[/b]. This is important, especially for a destro warlock, because when timing your rain of fire with the reset after you've grabbed the big guy, you need to know when to drop it while still being able to cross the gate before it latches. \r\n\r\nHope this helps.", "date": "2013-12-28T11:20:31-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 1936098, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "444745", "body": "Solo'd him as a Frost Mage today.  I was not able to use the strat below because the rune giants would keep despawing as soon as Thorim cast the spark.  Maybe I was doing something wrong, but I couldn't figure it out because I was doing exactly what the other strat said.  Instead I had to do the following:\n\n1. Kill the adds in the arena and open the gate. (same as kp202's strat)\n2. Run in the gate far enough to trigger the fight failure and make Thorim cast the spark, then run back into the arena to avoid the spark, running back into the hallway before the gate closes while leaving my pet in the arena. (also same as kp's strat)\n3. Once the fight resets, kill one mob with my elemental and resummon it.  The remaining arena mobs will run through the gate and you'll run to where the rune giant is.  As soon as you kill all of the arena mobs the fight will start and the rune giant in front of the door will become attackable.  [u]You now have until Thorim finishes his roleplay with Sif to kill both door giants and hit Thorim with an attack, and jump down.[/u]\n4. Once he jumps down you can kill him like normal.\n\nIn order to complete the part I underlined in time, I had to use Glyph of Blink, Glyph of Rapid Displacement, Blazing Speed, and a Swiftness Pot.  You also have to pretty much be able to one-shot the door giants; at 576 ilvl it was easy for me, but they only have 140k health or so on 10-man so a lesser geared mage can also do it if you have a couple of FoF/BR procs ready to go as soon as the first giant because attackable.  You can guarantee FoF procs by using your pet's freeze on the arena mobs.  After I killed the first giant I immediately blinked through the door as soon as it started opening, angling myself so I'd end up a little up the stairs.  I then popped the swiftness pot, used my FoF proc to kill the giant guarding the upper door, Blazing speed as soon as I got through it, then blink to cover the last bit of ground to hit Thorim before he finished his roleplay.  I jumped down and a moment later he jumped down with me, and then I finished the fight.", "date": "2014-01-20T02:20:09-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-01-20T02:21:51-06:00", 1, "444745"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 57, "id": 1946470, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Heffernan", "body": "Today I went for a quick run in 10-man and when I killed 3 watchers ( Hodir, Mimiron, Freya) a message appeared: \" The Ancient gate of keepers unlocks! \". It seems they solved the Thorim problem or is it just a bug.\nSo I could kill Vezaxx and Yogg without kill Thorim.", "date": "2014-02-24T19:01:56-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Tried his today and it does not work. Killed the 3 watchers and the door was still locked.", "creationdate": "2014-08-28T15:30:44-05:00", "id": 768164, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1946470, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "BChopper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I just opened the gate without killing Thorim. It opened soon as I killed Hodir (I killed Freya first, then Mimiron, then Hodir).", "creationdate": "2014-09-30T18:37:22-05:00", "id": 775954, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1946470, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "sakera", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-02-24T19:02:43-06:00", 1, "Heffernan"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 1947302, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arilwen", "body": "Craziness. I have tried this SIX times now as a DK using Death Siphon, Death's Advance, Icebound Fortitude, and Unholy Presence.\r\nFirst \"success\" was getting the big guy into arena. Didn't read guide well enough so... things respawned while I was out there. Killed, ran inside... no big guy. Just spark. Wee~\r\nSecond \"success\" just happened and was weirdness. Did it \"right\" this time... but missed with DnD and linked NO ONE. So I just ran up to Thorim.... who promptly challenged me (while untargetable) and jumped into the Arena with the giant worm and combatants. DING! \"Siffed\". Then everyone vanished. Gonna go kill Mir now and come back... see if he returned lol.", "date": "2014-02-27T21:10:09-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 59, "id": 1956685, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Virulent0", "body": "Soloed today as MM hunter w/o prof/race perks. Xexyz is right - door giant (now?) always despawns.  I tagged him, didn't tag him, and even killed him before spark initiation, and he always despawned, keeping the door closed.  So it's all about the P2 sprint from door giant to ledge.\r\n\r\nI used \r\n- posthaste (disengage speed boost)\r\n- glyph of disengage (distance boost)\r\n- glyph of pathfinding (speed boost)\r\n- glyph of black ice (ice trap speed boost)\r\n- glyph of aspect of cheetah (no daze)\r\n- swiftness potion\r\nI started [i]without[/i] my pet, to avoid having to revive or having LoS issues after the ledge.\r\n\r\n[b]P1a: Get Inside Door. [/b]Aspect of Iron Hawk (you don't need speed yet).  Kill P1 adds, open gate, survive the spark (don't even worry about the giant), trap the arena (explosive + snake), get inside door, wait for reset.\r\n\r\n[b]P1b: Ready to Run. [/b]Traps draw aggro.  Run to behind door giant, facing away from door.  I threw down a ice trap next to me for the glyph speed boost, and waited for melee P1 mob to activate the trap, but I didn't see if I got the boost or not.  Kill P1 mobs, but finish with full focus and chimera ready!\r\n\r\n[b]P2: RUN! [/b] P2 starts; speed is the key.  Chimera door giant, disengage through doorway, swiftness potion, pew-pew next giant, go through new door, NOW turn on cheetah (since you're past guards), jump/spin/disengage when it's cooled, run off ledge.\r\n\r\n[b]P3: Kill.[/b] Iron hawk, call pet, kill Thorim, get achieves, dance on corpse, celebrate.\r\n\r\nTook a while to get the timing right, but it worked.", "date": "2014-04-07T09:57:10-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Nice and concise description there, cheers :D", "creationdate": "2014-09-26T03:44:21-05:00", "id": 774277, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1956685, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bruceleroy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 60, "id": 1965185, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Paladestar", "body": "I soloed him today as a hunter.  It was so frustrating trying to find a good guide that makes every point crystal clear, but after a lot of trial and error I was eventually able to engage Thorim.  Hopefully my findings can help others who want to solo Thorim as a hunter.\r\n\r\nI played as BM so that I could have a spirit beast pet for the self-healing.  I had ilvl 578, but really gear isn\u2019t a problem here, the only hard part is being able to actually engage Thorim.\r\n\r\nMake sure that you have the [b]Glyph of disengage[/b] and the [b]Posthaste talent[/b].  You\u2019ll also need a stack of [b]Swiftness Potions[/b] (50% speed increase for 15 seconds) or a stack of [b]Darkwater potions[/b] (70% speed increase for 15 seconds).  Either potion kind is fine, but the 70% ones will allow you a greater margin for error.\r\n\r\n1. Observe the arena as you enter; some Iron dwarves are fighting a giant Jormungar.  Pick a spot where one of the dwarves is currently standing and memorise this location by the pattern on the floor of the arena.  You\u2019ll need to place an explosive trap here later.\r\n\r\n2. Move around the left side of the arena to the steps leading down to the tunnel/gauntlet.  Turn to face the enemies in the middle of the room.  Move to the right side of the steps as you face the enemies so that the lever that will later allow you to open the gate is in range.\r\n\r\n3. Misdirect to your pet and engage the enemies in the arena.\r\n\r\n4. As soon as the last enemy dies you will be able to interact with the lever, click it to begin a ten second cast to open the gate.  While this in progress put your pet on passive if it isn\u2019t already set this way.\r\n\r\n5. As soon as the gate opens disengage down the tunnel (your back should already be facing the gate due to your positioning from point number 2 above), turn the first corner and head towards the mini-boss at the end of this section of the gauntlet.\r\n\r\n6. Just before you reach the first row of dwarves cast Deterrence, this will prevent them from being able to hinder your movement.\r\n\r\n7. Just before the 60% movement speed bonus from the Posthaste talent runs out use your 50% or 70% move speed potion.\r\n\r\n8. Target the first gauntlet mini-boss as soon as you can, spam your Arcane Shot bind, so that as soon as the mini-boss is in range you\u2019ll attack it.\r\n\r\n9. As soon as you fire your arcane shot at the mini-boss turn around and run back to the arena you started in.  Disengage will come off of cooldown a couple of seconds after you fire your arcane shot so use it to help your speed if needed.  You can also use a second deterrence after you\u2019ve fired your shot at the mini-boss if you want to play it ultra-safe.\r\n\r\n10. You should easily make it back to the arena, but your pet may lag behind and die, not a big deal you can just revive it later, or if you manually activate Dash on your pet (assuming you use a spirit beast like I did) it\u2019ll catch up and get out of the gauntlet before the one-shot fight-reset lightning ball of doom catches up to it.\r\n\r\n11. Toss your explosive trap at the location you noted as indicated in point number 1 above.\r\n\r\n12. Get back inside the gauntlet before the gate closes, careful for the mini-boss\u2019s knockback, it can prevent you making it back through the gate in time.\r\n\r\n13. [b]You must not kill the mini-boss until the enemies in the main arena have respawned and the gate has closed.[/b]  When the enemies will respawn, they will trigger your explosive trap (if you placed it correctly) and start to follow you down the gauntlet as a result, they walk right through the closed gate.\r\n\r\n14. Kill the mini-boss and work your way through the gauntlet.  I didn\u2019t bother to kill any of the arena enemies at this stage, but if you have gear concerns and are worried about being overwhelmed later you can kill some of these now, just [b]make sure that at least one arena dwarf stays alive.[/b]\r\n\r\n15. Kill everything else in the gauntlet that is attackable, remembering to keep at least one arena dwarf alive.  Move into the room behind Thorim, avoid the two large circular traps on the floor.\r\n\r\n16. Once you\u2019re about half way along the room behind Thorim kill the remaining arena enemies that followed you through the gauntlet.  This will trigger a speech from Thorim.  Dismiss your pet now to play it safe, so that the silly thing doesn\u2019t get stuck when you later jump into the arena.\r\n\r\n17. This is the bit that frustrated me the most.  If you move too close to Thorim before Sif spawns he\u2019ll trigger the next phase, jump into the arena, but be unattackable, he\u2019ll then despawn and reset.  You must wait until Sif spawns before moving near him.  The problem with this is that as soon as Sif spawns Thorim will cast the one-shot lightning ball of doom and kill you.  You need perfect timing to get into the arena after Sif spawns but before the lightning orb can kill you.  I could never get it just right, too fast and Thorim remains unattackable, too slow and the lightning orb will kill you.  Then I had a nice idea, I made a macro:\r\n\r\n[code]/cast [harm] Disengage[/code]\r\n\r\nBind this macro to a key.  In the room behind Thorim note the small tiles on the floor, the trigger zone for the next phase is about 1 and a half small tiles before the start of the arch that links this room to the balcony where Thorim stands.  So to be totally safe, stand two rows of tiles from the edge of the arch, face into the room, so that the arch to the balcony is directly behind you.  [b]Target Thorim[/b] and spam the crap out of your disengage macro bind.  As soon as Sif spawns Thorim becomes attackable meeting the [harm] criteria of the macro, you\u2019ll disengage with perfect timing to not be too early or too late.  Run off the balcony as soon as you land from the disengage to make it into the arena before the lightning orb.  Easy mode!", "date": "2014-05-13T17:41:57-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I found this to work out rather well for myself as a fury warrior. Using Glyph of Death from Above, Double Time, n having the Evil Eye of Galakras almost seem like a requirement for this to be done. Heroic leap down the hall, use both charges to reach the first mini-boss and pull him out, heroic leaping. Once the encounter has about reset, drop mocking banner in the middle room then head back into the hallway... After you've completed Paladestar's steps 13-16, I personally just spammed charge instead of his disengage macro and that seemed to work out beautifully. Worked on the first go round.", "creationdate": "2014-06-12T15:43:20-05:00", "id": 750948, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1965185, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Itmstbmybday", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Excellent guide! really helped me a lot. after many attempts I just managed this on my hunter. I also managed to do it without engineering or speed pots. You can use Disengage again after having pulled the first mini-boss and just make it back to safety before getting hit by the lightening orb, this will only really work though if you get the timing perfect.", "creationdate": "2014-07-10T08:24:07-05:00", "id": 756486, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1965185, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mattous", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Main problem with this now is number 14. You have to kill all the mercenary's in the arena before you can even attack the mini-boss to open the first door.", "creationdate": "2014-08-18T01:37:48-05:00", "id": 765467, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1965185, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Vadel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 61, "id": 1986526, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "DNHalja", "body": "Okay, as a semi-geared Spriest, doing this solo was kind of a head turner, since I had no way to effectively grab the arena mobs when doing the Giant reset. BUT! I have found a way. After avoiding the giant ball of lightning death, go back INSIDE, and proceed the gauntlet as normal, WITHOUT killing any adds.\r\n\r\nReason being, is when you reach the top, you will need one crucial talent which is pretty often overlooked imo, because of its uselessness nowadays. Mind Control. When you pull the adds from the gauntlet with you, make sure you kill the melee, and kill all but 2 of the Dark Iron Acolyte, in case you mess up. MC one, go to the far edge, and use smite on the arena dark iron dwarf (It's 6 on the action bar). Done right, it should hit the dwarf. As soon as its finished casting, jump off with the MC. Done right, and it should aggro the arena mobs.\r\n\r\nProceed to kill Thorim and go about your merry way on trying to solo 25man yogg. Cheers!", "date": "2014-07-30T20:05:59-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "you can get a couple of trinkets that help a SP. tentacle from C'thun (AQ40) and terracota warrior from valley that you can use in arena. I went out and farmed both. I used the tentacle because its just stays in one place where you drop it, unlike the warrior which may follow you around.", "creationdate": "2014-08-05T05:34:22-05:00", "id": 762497, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1986526, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mecnunk", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 62, "id": 1995902, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kailhun", "body": "I'm having more trouble than usual with this one. I have the impression something has been changed. \r\nI'm a hunter and following Paladestar's 17 points. However the first mini-boss keeps resetting after point 12. I get back into the tunnel and there's no-one there. The mini-boss and dwarves respawn, but the mini-boss can't be attacked.\r\nWhen the NPC's in the Arena respawn they trigger the explosive-trap and come after me. Problem is the gate is closed and I can't get out. To activate the mini-boss I kill the Arena-NPC's, but as I can't get out and there's no-one in the arena the lightening bolt kills me.\r\n\r\nAny-one else noticed a change and have an idea how to adapt? So far, I haven't been able to find anything.", "date": "2014-08-25T03:57:26-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 63, "id": 2002708, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "666014", "body": "Prot paladins: [spell=54928] also works for tagging the arena mobs.", "date": "2014-09-14T15:45:55-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 64, "id": 2003369, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Gigabear", "body": "This encounter has been changed.  I was able to successfully solo it as a hunter using the following strategy:\n\nYou need to begin as normal, start by killing the arena mobs, opening the door with the lever, engaging the miniboss and then running back out into the arena before you get instagibbed by the deathball.  This next part is where it differs.  You need to set your pet in the center of the arena while the miniboss has aggro on it, then run back into the tunnel as soon as the deathball has passed.  The moment the gate comes down, kill the miniboss with the pet while both are on the other side of the gate and you are in the miniboss' tunnel.  This will open the first big door that is behind the first miniboss. The arena mobs will also have been reset, stopping deathballs from casting on you until they die again.\nNext, be sure the pet has pulled EVERYTHING in the arena, then spam follow and passive buttons to get the pet to warp past the door and come to you.\nTake the pet with you and kill the second mini boss.\nAfter you are near Thorim(not so close that he jumps down to the arena), you can finally kill all the arena adds the pet has had trailing it.  Once down, Sif will spawn and you can proceed as normal with the precise timing of getting Thorim to jump down to the arena floor whilst being attackable.", "date": "2014-09-16T23:46:52-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-09-16T23:51:04-05:00", 2, "Gigabear"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 2004041, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "midobu", "body": "Yup! After the new patch came at 10/15/14, the strategy for fighting with Thorim has changed! So I shall delete my old post here. \n\nHappy hunting for all!", "date": "2014-09-19T01:37:31-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "thank you for this post, this helped me a lot :)", "creationdate": "2014-09-26T03:26:46-05:00", "id": 774273, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2004041, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bruceleroy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-16T21:29:47-05:00", 45, "midobu"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 2013571, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "1170412", "body": "As of Patch 6.0.2 (Warlords of Draenor expansion pre-patch), this boss is completely solo-able without having to use any of the complicated strategies listed in other comments.  Just kill the initial adds in the arena, walk through the gauntlet and attack Thorim--he won't spawn his electric ball of death when you leave the arena any more.", "date": "2014-10-15T14:49:21-05:00", "rating": 77, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Fact. I just rolled through it with no issue on my Shadow Priest. (finally)", "creationdate": "2014-10-16T00:38:54-05:00", "id": 778992, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2013571, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Grenmoor66", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"Just kill the initial adds in the arena, walk through the gauntlet and attack Thorim\". What is that supposed to mean? Gauntlet? glove? Adds seemed to keep coming forever until I saw something on the floor which I clicked to open the back stairs passage, which I got stuck in. No help at all - downvoted.", "creationdate": "2015-07-06T09:25:38-05:00", "id": 882012, "rating": -14, "commentid": 2013571, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ludmillaa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Kill the trash in the arena, then open the gate using the lever to the left of it. Run through the tunnels, killing the mobs, and you'll come up behind Thorim. (Avoid the large circular areas on the floor of the hallway behind him! They'll stun you for a really long time!) Attack Thorim, then follow him when he jumps down into the arena and nuke him down. Waste no time following him; If he runs into the tunnel the encounter will reset and if you follow him in there, you can get stuck in the tunnel and have to hearth out.", "creationdate": "2015-07-10T03:34:08-05:00", "id": 883199, "rating": 22, "commentid": 2013571, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tygokoth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "A Gauntlet isn't just a glove, it's also a synonym (different word with the same meaning) for a difficult challenge. Often a life or death situation where time and skill are of the utmost importance. In this situation the moment you open the gate and get in the hallway you enter the Gauntlet. You used to have to split the raid, have half of them dodge insta-death lightning balls and kill minibosses while the rest kept the infinite spawning trash in the main room busy until the gauntlet group attacked Thorim to start Hard mode.", "creationdate": "2015-08-07T15:56:18-05:00", "id": 890240, "rating": 7, "commentid": 2013571, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Graknak", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 67, "id": 2013708, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "TomasValko", "body": "The nightmare is finally over - I can [b]confirm[/b] as of patch 6.0.2 the Thorim has been changed to allow players to solo him.\r\n\r\nIt's now very straightforward: kill arena mobs, pull lever, proceed down corridor and kill golem, run up the stairs, kill guardian, make your way to Thorim, give him a not-so-friendly tap on the back, then jump down and pew away.\r\n\r\nHappy Ulduar farming!", "date": "2014-10-15T18:24:35-05:00", "rating": 38, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Except as a Hunter I just tried exactly this and right as I jumped down and so did he in phase 2, he disappeared and the fight reset. I was even streaming to twitch so I have video to prove it. Man, what a buggy piece of crap fight. Edit: Apparently I need to dismiss my pet before I hit him in the back and jump down. Worked fine second attempt. Thanks for the info.", "creationdate": "2014-10-25T04:23:13-05:00", "id": 782025, "rating": 9, "commentid": 2013708, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "nirv", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I can confirm both issues. Yes, you can now solo without doing all the old tricks with speed boosts. And yes, and a hunter dismiss your pet, as else you'll hit a pet bug and the encounter will reset. So still some Blizzard habits never change ... :-)", "creationdate": "2014-11-08T20:56:45-06:00", "id": 787336, "rating": 6, "commentid": 2013708, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MarkusF", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yes theres a bug a thorim, when he jump down, you follow him then you stuck Inside, you cant attack mobs, its like a jail. Plus you cant use portal if you're a mage cuz you're in combat, THIS IS GAY! ~~ Solution: You have to jump down when thorim jump down. If you wait, the bug will happen or it will reset.", "creationdate": "2015-01-21T21:09:46-06:00", "id": 831046, "rating": -6, "commentid": 2013708, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Mystterious", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "^ Just happened to me. He jumped down and started heading down the hallway to reach me, so i headed back instead of jumping down with him. Suddenly i was trapped in the hall with the stairs and couldn't so anything. :/", "creationdate": "2015-01-23T21:48:22-06:00", "id": 831784, "rating": 4, "commentid": 2013708, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ortsac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He CAN be soloed. If you're ilvl is decent it's so easy it's unbelievable. What I did (balance druid) was wait for about 5 mobs to surround me (I take no damage) then cast Starfall and the entire group of them dies. So I went to the lever, waited for them to surround me, cast Starfall, pulled the lever, went inside. Easy.", "creationdate": "2018-05-01T23:51:19-05:00", "id": 1110731, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2013708, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Deliriium07", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 68, "id": 2126786, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kiyoine", "body": "No more arguing - Thorim is entirely soloable now. \r\n\r\nHowever, the only reason you might get stuck is waiting too long to begin pulling the lever. You should kill the trash close to where the lever sits, and [b]begin the cast to open the door AS SOON AS the trash is dead[/b]. Waiting too long to start results in getting stunned by Thorim's mace getting thrown at you, and/or adds jumping down from the arena to bother you.\r\n\r\nThankfully, I am a night elf and can justshadowmeld out to reset the encounter when I accidentally let that happen. Invisibility and Feign Death should also work.", "date": "2015-03-01T21:42:12-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
