{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 425522, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "106166", "body": "Loken is his brother - Which is an obvious reference to the two Norse gods Thor and Loke, or Loki as he is sometimes written.", "date": "2008-10-30T12:48:49-05:00", "rating": 27, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[u]loke is not thors brother[/u], he is odins (the king of the norse gods) half broter. and [u][b]loke is not a norse god [/b][/u]but a \"j\u00e6tte\" a kind of troll (the norse gods and \"j\u00e6tter\" are enemys)", "creationdate": "2009-03-07T10:41:12-06:00", "id": 392725, "rating": 2, "commentid": 425522, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bazze", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "J\u00e6tte/j\u00e4tte directly translated is giant.", "creationdate": "2009-03-16T05:51:45-05:00", "id": 394275, "rating": 2, "commentid": 425522, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Svettmormor", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Jotuns(excuse my writing) are giants but Loki is a frost giant. he was found and adopted by Odin Allfather, to, in future, hold him(again excuse my english), as a leverage against the frost giants whit which the gods are in war with. Instead he adopted him as his son and Thor's brother. Loki found out that he's a frost giant when he was a teenager ad so became the god of Chaos.", "creationdate": "2012-02-22T14:17:21-06:00", "id": 521743, "rating": 3, "commentid": 425522, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "921714", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Someone has been watching/reading too much Marvel... But at least, yes, please call them Jotuns at least, because translating J\u00e6tte with Giant or Frost Giant is... Lets just call it wrong. Jotuns/J\u00e6tter and Giants are two completely different things. Giants in norse mythology are so large, Thor once slept in a finger of a giants glove, whilst Jotuns are just slightly larger than Thor in size (they vary in size, but nowhere near giants). Most english translations ruins the 'lore' because they use the wrong terms. Marvel is just way off course - but intentionally so, just remember that...", "creationdate": "2012-07-04T07:12:40-05:00", "id": 554300, "rating": 3, "commentid": 425522, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Swampax", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
