{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 474316, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sasdeadeye", "body": "I've completed the quest chain involving Thorim and Loken, but i don't know what happened to Thorim. I saw Loken's golems take him away somewhere, but he seemed to still be alive at the time.\r\nI expected to find him with Loken in the Halls of Lightning, but no such luck.\r\nDoes anyone know where he is supposed to be now?\r\n(i may have missed something really obvious, i was tired when i did the quest chain)", "date": "2008-11-27T16:46:20-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He is confirmed a boss in Ulduar since [url=http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.html?topicId=15198911211&sid=1]17/02/2009[/url]. He, along with the other guardians ([url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Freya]Freya[/url], [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Hodir]Hodir[/url] and possibly also [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Mimir]Mimir[/url] and [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Tyr]Tyr[/url]) are bosses. If you have played through several [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Quest:Fate_of_the_Titans]questlines[/url] in Storm Peaks, you'll find out that someone, or something has driven away, kidnapped or otherwise occupied t", "creationdate": "2008-11-27T16:46:21-06:00", "id": 389341, "rating": 2, "commentid": 474316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "51581", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "More than likely he'll be one of those \"good guys gone bad\" bosses in the Uldar raid when 3.1 hits.  Whether you end up killing or saving him is completely up to blizzard, but considering how Norse mythology plays out... [small]*cough* Ragnarok *cough*[/small], I'm going to have to go with him dieing somewhere in the raid.", "creationdate": "2008-12-01T12:05:12-06:00", "id": 60966, "rating": 20, "commentid": 474316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "shadowaninja", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "wow, ur absolutely right, hes a boss in the Ulduar raid", "creationdate": "2009-04-14T19:22:02-05:00", "id": 399641, "rating": 1, "commentid": 474316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "268443", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just an update now that Ulduar's out- you have to beat him, Mimiron, Freya, and Hodir down before you can battle Yogg-Saron.  They'll help you in the fight if you aren't going for any of the achievements.", "creationdate": "2009-07-05T20:52:18-05:00", "id": 107930, "rating": 2, "commentid": 474316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "91650", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You actually need to free him from Yogg-Saron's grasp, and not kill him.", "creationdate": "2009-07-12T00:52:17-05:00", "id": 109190, "rating": 4, "commentid": 474316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "421755", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 475215, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "DJRavine", "body": "It's a simple traveling quest... \nbut it takes a while...\n\nHeres what to do...\n[ol]\n[li][/li]\n[li] Head to the top of the mountain, Temple Of Storms, accept the quest...[/li]\n[li] Fly down to Grom'arsh flight path....[/li]\n[li] Fly to Dun Nifflelem....[/li]\n[li] Talk to the King Jokkum, chat to him about the hammer...[/li]\n[li] You will them be placed upon his brow, and ferried to Thunderfall...[/li]\n[li]Thorin will appear on his drake you freed earlier...[/li]\n[li]They will have a D&M and then Thorin's Hammer will appear...[/li]\n[li]Talk to Thorin to complete the quest...[/li]\n[/ol]\n\ni hope that helped out.. ;)", "date": "2008-11-28T04:32:03-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-11-28T04:34:05-06:00", 2, "DJRavine"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 489045, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "264034", "body": "Thor and Loki is not brothers , Loki and Odin are blood brothers and Odin is Thor's father. In some stories Loki is a troll , wich in norse mythology is the bad counterpart for the humans.", "date": "2008-12-04T07:31:37-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I don't know about the official and actual Norse Mythology, but in more popularised versions of it, Loki and Thor are brothers, not blood brothers though, as in Loki was the son of a great frost giant found on a battlefield(quite odd for WoW though, since if anything it would seem reverse here, and that Thorim is the closest to being any relation to the frost giants). This is how it is in Marvel's Thor universe, which may differ dramatically in origins(though lots of naming and structure of the Norse Mythology is retained in this series). There's a part of me that is hoping blizzard makes him ", "creationdate": "2008-12-04T07:31:38-06:00", "id": 374195, "rating": 1, "commentid": 489045, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "184400", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "They're brothers (brother/sister after a recent development...) in Marvel, though!", "creationdate": "2008-12-04T18:07:05-06:00", "id": 367157, "rating": 1, "commentid": 489045, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "154163", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 497238, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "170066", "body": "If you want to open up quests with Thorim and haven't quested in Storm Peaks, go to K3. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=29473]Gretchen Fizzlespark[/url] will give you quest [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=12843]They Took Our Men![/url]\r\n\r\nThis will open up long chain which at [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=12886]The Drakkensryd[/url], will let you to talk with Thorim. \r\n\r\nTake a notice that this is only if you haven't done any quests for him, as he seems to be in different places as a story progresses.", "date": "2008-12-08T05:47:37-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 548165, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "45715", "body": "Some background info: \r\nThis NPC is a clear referance to the nordic god, Thor. His wife was even named Sif, just like Thorim's wife. (Thor's wife wasn't slain by any of his brothers, though)\r\nBut then again, a lot of stuff in Northrend is inspired by nordic mythologies, like the Valkyries that Arthas uses, Loken(Loki, or as he was named in Scandinavia, Loke) and a lot of other obvious referances.", "date": "2009-01-05T12:39:03-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
