{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 497234, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "170066", "body": "If you want to open up quests with Thorim and haven't quested in Storm Peaks, go to K3. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=29473]Gretchen Fizzlespark[/url] will give you quest [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=12843]They Took Our Men![/url]\r\n\r\nThis will open up long chain which at [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=12886]The Drakkensryd[/url], will let you to talk with Thorim. \r\n\r\nTake a notice that this is only if you haven't done any quests for him, as he seems to be in different places as a story progresses.", "date": "2008-12-08T05:46:31-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 548158, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "45715", "body": "In case no one had noticed, this NPC is a clear referance to the nordic god, Thor. His wife was even named Sif, just like Thorim's wife. (Thor's wife wasn't slain by any of his brothers, though)\r\nBut then again, a lot of stuff in Northrend is inspired by nordic mythologies, like the Valkyries that Arthas uses, Loken(Loki, or as he was named in Scandinavia, Loke) and a lot of other obvious referances.", "date": "2009-01-05T12:35:17-06:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "His hammer (Kromir) also takes the name almost exactly of Thor's Mighty Hammer. He also has the same title as Thor; [i]The Stormlord[/i]. And he lives atop a tall mountain, like Thor.", "creationdate": "2009-01-09T19:54:21-06:00", "id": 379166, "rating": 0, "commentid": 548158, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "202004", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Um, Thor does not have a title. He's just Thor. He is responsible for lightning (the sparks from his hammer as he swings it) and thunder (the hooves of the goats pulling his cart)  He doesn't live atop a tall mountain either, he lives in Valhalla, which is another plane of existence.  Think you're thinking of Zeus, the Greek god.", "creationdate": "2009-01-16T06:57:41-06:00", "id": 380911, "rating": 2, "commentid": 548158, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "SimonPip", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He sits on a thrown in the middle of the temple of storms", "creationdate": "2009-01-29T19:45:05-06:00", "id": 384586, "rating": 1, "commentid": 548158, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "133798", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "simon, why so negative?  Thor is the god of thunder and Thorim is on the Temple of Storms.  Thorim doesn't like Giants and neither did Thor.  Thorim has a wife named Sif just like Thor.  This is obviously  reference, so don't be so nitpicky with other peoples comments just to make yourself sound smart.", "creationdate": "2009-03-14T19:50:00-05:00", "id": 85526, "rating": 6, "commentid": 548158, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "282259", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Loki? that's unusual ... in my country loki means toilet O.o", "creationdate": "2011-05-04T14:26:20-05:00", "id": 241827, "rating": 0, "commentid": 548158, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "fiojam930", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
